# Per-release extras files live in this directory.
#
# Convention: .github/release-extras/<tag>.md (e.g. v2026.5.5.5.md). If the
# file exists when the release workflow runs, its contents are appended below
# the auto-generated changelog slice with a `---` separator and an
# `## Additional notes` heading.
#
# Use only for content that genuinely cannot be captured in commit subjects:
# server-side coordination notes, migration instructions, links to a wiki
# page that has the long-form details, etc. Anything that IS a code change
# should land as a conventional-commit subject and let the auto-generator
# pick it up.
#
# The same scrub gates (ASCII normalisation, voice + internal-only-vocabulary
# check) run on the composed body, so an em-dash or a phrase like the
# stock-marketing word for "covering everything" in an extras file fails
# the workflow just as it would in a commit subject.
#
# See .github/RELEASE_WORKFLOW.md for the full policy.
